                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7357/185.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dodge states that the consul at Tegucigalpa reports the cancellation by the
                    Honduranean Government of the exequaturs of the American consul and vice consul
                    at Ceiba, as well as that of the French consular agent. Mr. Dodge says no reason
                    is given for this step, but it is presumably on account of the action lately
                    taken by the consular officials mentioned, which was previously reported to
                    department by the consul.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
